text:
'Cangjie programming language_range_range_type': 'In Cangjie code language, The Range<T> type in Cangjie represents a sequence of values with a fixed step size. It is a generic type where T must support relational operators and can be added to an Int64 value. The most commonly used instance is Range<Int64>, which represents a sequence of integers.'

Code_Example:
let r1: Range<Int64> = Range<Int64>(0, 10, 1, true, true, true)
let r2: Range<Int64> = Range<Int64>(0, 10, 1, true, true, false)
let r3: Range<Int64> = Range<Int64>(10, 0, -2, true, true, false)
